<p><img src="https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/1/1/d/event_509060765.jpeg" border="0" hspace="8" vspace="8" /><br /><strong><br />Narrowing the skills gap, one chapter at a time.</strong><br /><br /><strong> </strong>Welcome to <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/events/290173641/">API a la Mode, Season 2</a></strong>. Eight Boston PHP members have signed up to participate in <strong>Season 2</strong>. We will conduct four sprints. Each sprint will last one week. By the end we will have completed nearly three hours of API training and earned a certificate we can add to our LinkedIn profiles.<br /><br />Begin by gaining access to <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/learning/practice-it-go-rest-api-server">Practice It: Go REST API Server</a></strong>—a <em>free </em><strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/learning/">LinkedIn Learning</a></strong> course integrated with <strong><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yHIpkXWQgAI">GitHub Codespaces</a></strong>. Then proceed to the <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53793232">Introduce Yourself</a></strong> discussion area on the Boston PHP Meetup website.<br /><br />The <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53793724">Master Discussion List</a></strong> contains links to the discussion areas for each of the four sprints. Feel free to bookmark this <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53793724">Master Discussion List</a></strong> for easy access. Once you complete the first sprint, post an update in <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53793768">Sprint #1: Some Basics</a></strong>. If you have any questions about how to proceed, please post a message in the <strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/53793232">Introduce Yourself</a></strong> discussion area.<br /><br />Let's <span style="background-color: #f6f7f8; font-family: &quot;Graphik Meetup&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">have API (a pie)</span>.</p>
